chunk_content: H O Report all HRH at those sites who are working in HIV-related activities, regardless of whether they are S T supported by PEPFAR or not. C PEPFAR team should collect and report on this data during the last quarter of the year. Ideally this O U data would come from a MOH HRIS/HRID system, or a payroll system from a Ministry of Finance. N T Total number of health workers should be reported. Report HRH who are actively working on services R or programs related to HIV at the time of data collection, not including staff who have resigned, Y absconded, are dismissed, are pending hiring, or are on extended leave (e.g., for graduate studies). I N Unfilled positions or vacancies should not be included. D I If possible, avoid collecting data across a period which spans across a major budgetary change or a C health worker graduation and placement period.
